Installation & Setup


1. In the command line, type following:
curl https://install.meteor.com/ | sh
(Windows folks go here: https://www.meteor.com/install)

2. Go to the folder in the command line:
cd TweetMinerClient

3. Adding bootstrap package in the command line, type following:
meteor add twbs:bootstrap

4. Building the application, type the following command in the command line:
meteor

5. After the terminal showing the following text:
=> Started proxy.
=> Started MongoDB.
=> Started your app.

=> App running at: http://localhost:3000/

Go to local host by visit "http://localhost:3000/" in the browser.